---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Loan Against Property | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Loan Against Property</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Loan Against Property</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Unlock the value of your property with competitive interest rates. Get high-value loans for business expansion, education, medical emergencies, or any personal needs.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i> Up to ₹10 Cr
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i> Low Interest 8.5%+
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-calendar-check"></i> Long Tenure
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>Loan Against Property Overview</h2>
          <p>A Loan Against Property (LAP) is a secured loan where you pledge your residential or commercial property as collateral to avail funds from a bank or NBFC. Since the loan is backed by property, lenders offer higher loan amounts at lower interest rates compared to unsecured loans like personal loans.</p>
          <p>LAP is ideal for individuals and businesses who need large funds for purposes such as business expansion, higher education, medical treatment, debt consolidation, or working capital. The loan amount typically ranges from 50% to 70% of the market value of the property, and repayment tenures can extend up to 15 years.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">8.5%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Interest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹10 Cr</span>
              <span class="info-label">Maximum Loan Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">15 Yrs</span>
              <span class="info-label">Maximum Tenure</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Loan Against Property Interest Rates 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Max Loan Amount</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI</td>
                <td>8.70% onwards</td>
                <td>₹7.5 Crore</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Bank</td>
                <td>8.50% onwards</td>
                <td>₹10 Crore</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>8.90% onwards</td>
                <td>₹5 Crore</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Bajaj Finserv</td>
                <td>9.00% onwards</td>
                <td>₹5 Crore</td>
                <td>12 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>IIFL Finance</td>
                <td>9.20% onwards</td>
                <td>₹10 Crore</td>
                <td>15 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Salaried individuals with a minimum monthly income of ₹25,000</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Self-employed professionals and businesspersons with a minimum annual income of ₹3 Lakh</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Age between 21 to 65 years at the time of loan maturity</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> CIBIL score of 650 or above preferred by most lenders</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Property must have a clear title with no legal disputes</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Property should be located within city limits or approved municipal areas</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Property Types Accepted</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-building"></i> Residential apartments and independent houses</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-store"></i> Commercial properties such as offices, shops, and showrooms</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-industry"></i> Industrial properties and manufacturing units</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-map"></i> Residential or commercial plots with approved construction plans</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-warehouse"></i> Warehouses and godowns in industrial zones</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Apply for Loan Against Property</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Check Eligibility</h4>
              <p>Use our eligibility calculator to check your loan amount and verify your property qualifies for the loan.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Submit Application</h4>
              <p>Fill out the online application form with your personal, financial, and property details accurately.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Property Valuation</h4>
              <p>The lender will conduct a property valuation and technical assessment to determine the loan amount.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Get Disbursal</h4>
              <p>Once approved, the loan amount is disbursed directly to your bank account within 7-10 working days.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Identity proof: Aadhaar card, PAN card, passport, or voter ID</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Address proof: Aadhaar, utility bills, passport, or rental agreement</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Income proof: Salary slips (last 3 months) or ITR (last 2 years) for self-employed</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Bank statements of the last 6 months showing regular transactions</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Property documents: Title deed, sale deed, building plan approval, encumbrance certificate</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Property tax receipts and latest valuation report</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Passport-size photographs (2 copies)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Apply for Loan Against Property</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Property Type</option>
                  <option value="residential">Residential</option>
                  <option value="commercial">Commercial</option>
                  <option value="industrial">Industrial</option>
                  <option value="plot">Plot / Land</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Property Value (₹)" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block">Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/personal-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Personal Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Page CTA -->
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Ready to Unlock Your Property's Value?</h3>
          <p>Get the best loan against property offers with competitive rates and flexible tenures.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Talk to Expert <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">FAQs</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know about Loan Against Property</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What is the maximum loan amount I can get against my property? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">The maximum loan amount depends on the market value of your property and the lender's Loan-to-Value (LTV) ratio. Typically, banks offer 50% to 70% of the property's market value. For premium properties in metro cities, you can get up to ₹10 Crore from lenders like HDFC Bank and IIFL Finance.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I continue to live in my property after taking a loan against it? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, absolutely. You retain full possession and usage rights of your property throughout the loan tenure. The lender only holds the property documents as security. You can continue living in or using the property as before. However, you cannot sell or transfer ownership until the loan is fully repaid.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What happens if I default on my Loan Against Property EMI payments? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">If you default on EMI payments, the lender will first send reminders and notices. Continued default may lead to penalties, a negative impact on your CIBIL score, and ultimately the lender may initiate legal proceedings under the SARFAESI Act to auction the property to recover the outstanding amount. It is advisable to communicate with your lender early if you face financial difficulties.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Is prepayment or foreclosure allowed on Loan Against Property? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, most lenders allow prepayment and foreclosure of LAP. For floating rate loans, as per RBI guidelines, no prepayment penalty can be charged. For fixed rate loans, a nominal foreclosure charge of 2-4% of the outstanding amount may apply. Partial prepayments can significantly reduce your interest burden over the loan tenure.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What is the difference between Loan Against Property and a Home Loan? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">A Home Loan is specifically used to purchase, construct, or renovate a residential property, while a Loan Against Property can be used for any purpose — business, education, medical expenses, or personal needs. LAP typically has slightly higher interest rates than home loans (8.5% vs 8.25%) but offers more flexibility in end-use. Home loans also offer higher tax benefits under Section 24(b) and Section 80C of the Income Tax Act.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
